cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with object detection, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). It also addresses the issue of domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel method that involves weak self-training and adversarial background score regularization, which are both techniques used in deep learning (cs.AI). The paper also presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
